{
  "title": "SceneTransitionLifecycleError",
  "description": "Thrown when a SceneTransitionSession or SceneTransitionEnvironment violates the transition lifecycle contract: - `'commit-reentrant'` — SceneTransitionEnvironment.commit was called a second time on the same session. Dev-mode only; a production build no-ops the second call instead of throwing. - `'done-before-commit'` — the session reported SceneTransitionSession.done `true` while SceneTransitionEnvironment.committed was still `false`. Always thrown, dev and production — the navigation aborts and the session is destroyed. - `'aborted'` — the owning `SceneDirector` was destroyed while this session was still active. Always thrown.",
  "symbol": "SceneTransitionLifecycleError",
  "kind": "class",
  "subsystem": "core",
